This paper is about optimizing experience replay in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel framework for experience replay optimization and conducts experiments on various continuous control tasks. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
